article.headline: Maine 60, Kennesaw State 47
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Mark Socoby scored 16 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Maine beat Kennesaw State 60-47 in the 100 Club Classic on Saturday night. Troy Barnies, who as 8-of-8 from the field, finished with 16 points for the Black Bears (2-0). The Owls (1-1) shot just 27 percent from the field, making only 16-for-60 shots from the floor. Jon-Michael Nickerson led Kennesaw State with 14 points. Kelvin McConnell had 12 points for the Owls, who n couldn't pull within seven points of Maine in the second half. Maine opened the second half with a 9-0 run to build a 14-point lead. The Black Bears committed 23 turnovers and Kennesaw State out rebounded Maine -- 19-8.
